}}'''''Marie Tudor''''' is a 1912 French [[silent film|silent]] [[historical film]] directed by [[Albert Capellani]] and starring [[Jeanne Delvair]], [[Paul Capellani]] and [[Romuald Joubé]]. The film is an adaptation of [[Victor Hugo]]'s 1833 [[Marie Tudor|play of the same title]] set at the court of [[Mary I of England]].<ref>Parill & Robison p.143-44</ref> It was re-released in 1917, and is sometimes dated to that year.

==Cast==
* [[  Jeanne Delvair]] as Marie Tudor  
* [[Paul Capellani]] as Fabiano Fabiani  
* [[Romuald Joubé]] as Gilbert  
* [[Léon Bernard]]
* [[Andrée Pascal]]
* [[Léa Piron]]  
* [[Henri-Amédée Charpentier]] 

